00:15:22.756 --> 00:15:25.759 position:50% align:center
He was a beautiful boy.

00:15:25.842 --> 00:15:27.093 position:50% align:center
So when this one is born,

00:15:27.177 --> 00:15:28.595 position:50% align:center
I'm going to give
them all the love

00:15:28.678 --> 00:15:31.222 position:50% align:center
that their big
brother couldn't get.

00:15:36.186 --> 00:15:37.937 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:15:45.445 --> 00:15:47.906 position:50% align:center
I can't explain it,

00:15:47.989 --> 00:15:50.992 position:50% align:center
but I just know
everything'll be okay.

00:15:53.161 --> 00:15:55.663 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Of course it will!

00:15:55.747 --> 00:15:59.709 position:50% align:center
And I promise I'll learn how
to change diapers for you!

00:15:59.793 --> 00:16:01.461 position:50% align:center
[ARAI]
I'll hold you to that!

00:16:01.544 --> 00:16:02.921 position:50% align:center
--[HANA] I'll do everything!

00:16:03.004 --> 00:16:05.757 position:50% align:center
--[ARAI] C'mon, don't cry.
--[HANA] I'll do everything!

00:16:11.429 --> 00:16:13.723 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:16:13.807 --> 00:16:15.350 position:50% align:center
[MIKO chuckles]

00:16:44.629 --> 00:16:46.631 position:50% align:center
[POLE MONSTER 08A]
Help me.

00:16:46.715 --> 00:16:51.094 position:50% align:center
Help me. Help me.

00:16:51.177 --> 00:16:53.805 position:50% align:center
Help me.

00:16:59.102 --> 00:17:01.688 position:50% align:center
[POLE MONSTER 08A]
Help me.

00:17:01.771 --> 00:17:03.815 position:50% align:center
Help me.

00:17:03.898 --> 00:17:05.775 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
What are all these things?

00:17:05.859 --> 00:17:07.944 position:50% align:center
Where do they come from?

00:17:10.405 --> 00:17:14.242 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Why did I start to see them?

00:17:14.325 --> 00:17:16.703 position:50% align:center
[POLE MONSTER 08A]
Help me.

00:17:16.786 --> 00:17:19.873 position:50% align:center
Help me...

00:17:19.956 --> 00:17:22.083 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I don't know what I should do.

00:17:22.167 --> 00:17:27.672 position:50% align:center
Is it better to face them
instead of ignoring them?

00:17:27.756 --> 00:17:30.300 position:50% align:center
That's what Yulia does

00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:34.387 position:50% align:center
and that old lady
who gave me those beads.

00:17:34.471 --> 00:17:36.681 position:50% align:center
I should have
a little more courage.

00:17:36.765 --> 00:17:39.309 position:50% align:center
I should stop turning away.

00:17:40.852 --> 00:17:42.103 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:48.485 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MONSTER 08A sucking]

00:17:52.697 --> 00:17:53.615 position:50% align:center
[MIKO whimpers]

00:17:53.698 --> 00:17:56.951 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MONSTER 08A groans]

00:18:00.914 --> 00:18:05.627 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Face it... head on.

00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:09.464 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MONSTER 08A]
I want warm.

00:18:09.547 --> 00:18:12.676 position:50% align:center
I want cold.

00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:17.806 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MONSTER 08A]
Huh?

00:18:19.557 --> 00:18:22.435 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Mm... Nope. Not this one.

00:18:22.519 --> 00:18:24.896 position:50% align:center
No idea how to deal with this.

00:18:33.613 --> 00:18:36.658 position:50% align:center
Red-bean soup's
always good, right?

00:18:36.741 --> 00:18:39.077 position:50% align:center
[VENDING MONSTER 08A]
Warm.

00:18:42.706 --> 00:18:45.375 position:50% align:center
[HANA] I went to get a soda from
the vending machine yesterday,

00:18:45.458 --> 00:18:48.586 position:50% align:center
and you won't
believe what happened!

00:18:48.670 --> 00:18:51.881 position:50% align:center
Ugh! There was this
ginormous moth on it!

00:18:51.965 --> 00:18:54.259 position:50% align:center
Sitting right on top
of the button, too!

00:18:54.342 --> 00:18:55.468 position:50% align:center
Freaked me out!

00:18:55.552 --> 00:18:57.554 position:50% align:center
But you still wanted a soda.

00:18:57.637 --> 00:18:58.805 position:50% align:center
Did you press it anyway?

00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:00.557 position:50% align:center
Are you out of your mind?!

00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:01.725 position:50% align:center
If I had touched that thing,

00:19:01.808 --> 00:19:04.352 position:50% align:center
it would've flown
directly into my face!

00:19:04.436 --> 00:19:05.812 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Mm...

00:19:05.895 --> 00:19:07.939 position:50% align:center
I went to the convenience
store to get a soda instead.

00:19:08.023 --> 00:19:11.276 position:50% align:center
"Let sleeping moths lie"
as the saying goes!

00:19:11.359 --> 00:19:12.819 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I see.

00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:15.530 position:50% align:center
Also, a perfectly good solution.

00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:17.365 position:50% align:center
Hmm.

00:19:17.449 --> 00:19:20.994 position:50% align:center
Maybe I had it right.
Thanks for the advice.

00:19:21.077 --> 00:19:24.414 position:50% align:center
[HANA] Hm? That wasn't
advice, but whatever!

00:19:26.291 --> 00:19:28.710 position:50% align:center
Hey, I think our
new teacher's here.

00:19:28.793 --> 00:19:30.170 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
That was today, huh?

00:19:30.253 --> 00:19:32.172 position:50% align:center
[footsteps]

00:19:32.255 --> 00:19:34.132 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:38.553 --> 00:19:41.931 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Mrs. Arai is on maternity leave,

00:19:42.015 --> 00:19:44.100 position:50% align:center
so for the time being,

00:19:44.184 --> 00:19:47.187 position:50% align:center
I'll be taking over as
your homeroom teacher.

00:19:50.815 --> 00:19:52.609 position:50% align:center
My name is Zen Toono.

00:19:52.692 --> 00:19:56.029 position:50% align:center
Thank you all for
having me here.

00:19:56.112 --> 00:19:57.989 position:50% align:center
Well, I'd be glad to take him.

00:19:58.073 --> 00:20:00.992 position:50% align:center
[HANA gasps]
Promise to treat him well?

00:20:01.076 --> 00:20:03.078 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Not this guy.

00:20:04.120 --> 00:20:06.414 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
No, I refuse.

00:20:06.498 --> 00:20:08.833 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
He's kinda hot, huh?

00:20:08.917 --> 00:20:09.918 position:50% align:center
[YAMAZAKI]
Thirsty much?

00:20:10.001 --> 00:20:11.002 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 08A]
Wonder how old he is.

00:20:11.086 --> 00:20:12.671 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 08B]
He seems pretty chill.

00:20:12.754 --> 00:20:15.048 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 08C]
I was worried.

00:20:15.131 --> 00:20:18.134 position:50% align:center
Hold on, I know that guy!

00:20:21.471 --> 00:20:26.476 position:50% align:center
[CAT MONSTERS groaning]

00:22:11.498 --> 00:22:15.585 position:50% align:center
[DOGS yipping]

00:22:15.669 --> 00:22:20.465 position:50% align:center
[GOUZUKA grunts]

00:22:20.548 --> 00:22:22.133 position:50% align:center
[SHOP LADY 08A]
Sir, that man hasn't moved

00:22:22.217 --> 00:22:23.760 position:50% align:center
for the last ten minutes!

00:22:23.843 --> 00:22:26.096 position:50% align:center
Shh! He's inspecting
the cat food!

00:22:26.179 --> 00:22:28.431 position:50% align:center
If we interrupt him,
we're both dead!

00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:35.855 position:50% align:center
[GOUZUKA]
Huh...

00:22:37.107 --> 00:22:38.650 position:50% align:center
I'll take this, please.

00:22:38.733 --> 00:22:41.069 position:50% align:center
[SHOP MAN 08A, SHOP LADY 08A]
Absolutely. Thanks so much.

00:22:44.030 --> 00:22:47.534 position:50% align:center
[GOUZUKA grunts]

00:22:50.495 --> 00:22:53.331 position:50% align:center
I'll have this one, please.
With the little pink bears.

00:22:53.415 --> 00:22:56.209 position:50% align:center
Right! A fine choice, sir!

00:23:01.840 --> 00:23:03.174 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:23:03.258 --> 00:23:04.968 position:50% align:center
[GOUZUKA chuckles]

00:23:05.051 --> 00:23:07.721 position:50% align:center
Aw, you like that,
little Nyansuke?

00:23:08.888 --> 00:23:12.142 position:50% align:center
They really used
to love that stuff, too.

00:23:24.112 --> 00:23:25.488 position:50% align:center
[GOUZUKA grunts]

00:23:30.285 --> 00:23:32.787 position:50% align:center
[GOUZUKA] Happy anniversary.

00:23:36.291 --> 00:23:39.002 position:50% align:center
[JUNJI] We all got someone we
never wanna see again, right?

00:23:39.085 --> 00:23:40.712 position:50% align:center
Well, go figure,
those are the ones

00:23:40.795 --> 00:23:42.464 position:50% align:center
you always end up bumping into!

00:23:42.547 --> 00:23:45.133 position:50% align:center
Next time:
"Things She's Seen Before"!

00:23:45.216 --> 00:23:47.010 position:50% align:center
Running into some
creep at high school?

00:23:47.093 --> 00:23:49.554 position:50% align:center
Sends a chill down my spine!